HEADWORD: Flightiness
<hw>Flight"i*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or quality of being
flighty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>flightness</qex> of her temper.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Levity; giddiness; volatility; lightness;
wildness; eccentricity. See <er>Levity</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flight-shot</ent>⟦br⟧
